Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so as you know from your research,\N{\rChinese}好的，正如你在研究中所知，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.66,0:00:04.94,English,,0,0,0,,on April 1st,\N{\rChinese}在4月1日，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.94,0:00:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,the Israelis struck the Iranian embassy in Damascus,\N{\rChinese}以色列人袭击了驻大马士的伊朗大使馆，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:14.08,English,,0,0,0,,Syria, killing seven people, including two commanders.\N{\rChinese}叙利亚，杀死七人，其中两名指挥官。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.16,0:00:19.02,English,,0,0,0,,This is an act of war because the embassy is considered Iranian territory.\N{\rChinese}这是一场战争行动，因为大使馆被视为伊朗领土。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.74,0:00:23.30,English,,0,0,0,,And never before has this been done intentionally.\N{\rChinese}此举从未有过先例。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.30,0:00:24.84,English,,0,0,0,,And\N{\rChinese}和
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:28.52,English,,0,0,0,,this follows the killing,\N{\rChinese}随后是他们将军官卡塞姆·苏莱曼尼于2020年被暗杀的事件。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.70,0:00:32.60,English,,0,0,0,,the assassination of their general, Qasem Soleimani, in 2020.\N{\rChinese}the assassination of their general, Qasem Soleimani, in 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.40,0:00:38.86,English,,0,0,0,,This is when the Americans launched a drone strike against him in Baghdad.\N{\rChinese}这时美国在巴格达对他发动无人机打击。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.08,0:00:44.22,English,,0,0,0,,And he was really one of the top Iranian generals.\N{\rChinese}他确实是伊朗最顶尖的将领之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.30,0:00:50.30,English,,0,0,0,,And what both of these incidents show us is\N{\rChinese}这两件事都向我们展示了……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.30,0:00:52.80,English,,0,0,0,,that the Americans and the Israelis,\N{\rChinese}美国人和以色列人，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.30,0:00:55.74,English,,0,0,0,,have dominance over Iran, okay?\N{\rChinese}对伊朗拥有优势，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:57.46,English,,0,0,0,,So military dominance.\N{\rChinese}于是军事优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,So the first thing is they have technology, right?\N{\rChinese}所以第一件事是他们有技术，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.72,0:01:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,So technologically,\N{\rChinese}所以从技术上说，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.40,0:01:10.86,English,,0,0,0,,America and Israel are so much superior to Iran.\N{\rChinese}美国和以色列在技术上远超伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.60,0:01:15.88,English,,0,0,0,,So that there's a jet that went from Israel\N{\rChinese}于是有一架飞机从以色列起飞
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.46,0:01:19.66,English,,0,0,0,,and went to Damascus to carry out the strike.\N{\rChinese}并飞往大马士干执行打击。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.98,0:01:22.42,English,,0,0,0,,Now, if you did the research, you would know that\N{\rChinese}现在，如果你做过研究，你就会知道
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.30,0:01:26.26,English,,0,0,0,,the Canadian embassy is right next to the Iranian embassy.\N{\rChinese}加拿大大使馆就在伊朗大使馆旁边。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.40,0:01:31.14,English,,0,0,0,,And the strike was\N{\rChinese}而这次打击是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.14,0:01:35.60,English,,0,0,0,,so precise that it only hit the Iranian embassy and didn't touch anything else, okay?\N{\rChinese}精准到只击中伊朗大使馆，没碰到其他地方，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.76,0:01:36.98,English,,0,0,0,,That's a precision strike.\N{\rChinese}这是一记精准打击。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:41.76,English,,0,0,0,,That's how powerful the technology that the Americans and the Israelis have, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是美国和以色列拥有的技术有多强大，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.92,0:01:45.06,English,,0,0,0,,But the other thing that's important is the idea of intelligence.\N{\rChinese}但另一件重要的事是情报的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.88,0:01:53.28,English,,0,0,0,,So how do the Israelis know that, okay, they're not going to attack Iran?\N{\rChinese}那么以色列是怎么知道他们不去打伊朗的？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.30,0:01:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,And how do they know that these commanders would be there at that time, right?\N{\rChinese}他们又是怎么知道这些指挥官会在那个时间到场的？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.26,0:01:59.78,English,,0,0,0,,That's intelligence. And intelligence comes in two forms, right?\N{\rChinese}这就是情报，情报有两种形式，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.06,0:02:04.22,English,,0,0,0,,There's the idea of human, and then signals.\N{\rChinese}有了人力情报，再加上信号情报。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.94,0:02:08.10,English,,0,0,0,,Signals is basically, I can listen in on your cell phone.\N{\rChinese}信号情报基本就是我能监听你的手机。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:09.54,English,,0,0,0,,I can track where you go.\N{\rChinese}我能追踪你去哪里。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.72,0:02:11.50,English,,0,0,0,,I know where your car is, right?\N{\rChinese}我知道你车在哪里，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.66,0:02:14.38,English,,0,0,0,,That's signals, electronic intelligence.\N{\rChinese}那是信号情报，电子情报。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.74,0:02:17.80,English,,0,0,0,,The other is human. So there are spies in the embassy\N{\rChinese}另一种是人力情报。所以大使馆里有间谍。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.80,0:02:21.70,English,,0,0,0,,who tell the Israelis that this meeting will happen, okay?\N{\rChinese}谁告诉以色列人这次会晌会发生，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:23.28,English,,0,0,0,,So this is clearly, you know, a very important part of the story.\N{\rChinese}所以这显然是个非常重要的环节，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.28,0:02:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,So the Israeli military dominance that Israel and\N{\rChinese}所以以色列的军事实力，正是…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.40,0:02:28.36,English,,0,0,0,,the Americans possess over Iran.\N{\rChinese}美国在伊朗拥有超过…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.32,0:02:33.22,English,,0,0,0,,And when this strike happened,\N{\rChinese}当这次打击发生时，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:37.72,English,,0,0,0,,as you know, the Iranians had to respond.\N{\rChinese}正如你所知，伊朗人必须作出回应。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.06,0:02:39.88,English,,0,0,0,,And this was called Operation True Promise.\N{\rChinese}并且这被称为“真诺之约”行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.12,0:02:43.48,English,,0,0,0,,And the idea of True Promise was that\N{\rChinese}而“真诺之约”的想法是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.48,0:02:47.22,English,,0,0,0,,there's a strike package,\N{\rChinese}有一套打击方案，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:49.26,English,,0,0,0,,okay,\N{\rChinese}好的，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.86,0:02:52.34,English,,0,0,0,,consisting of 300 drones.\N{\rChinese}共300架无人机。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.26,0:02:55.62,English,,0,0,0,,And missiles\N{\rChinese}以及导弹。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.62,0:02:58.34,English,,0,0,0,,that hit Israel.\N{\rChinese}击中以色列。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:01.96,English,,0,0,0,,Now, what the Israelis say is that\N{\rChinese}现在，以色列人说的是
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:06.14,English,,0,0,0,,99% of these drones and missiles were intercepted.\N{\rChinese}99%的这些无人机和导弹被拦截。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.14,0:03:08.80,English,,0,0,0,,They caused no damage. And\N{\rChinese}他们没有造成任何损失。并且
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.80,0:03:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,the Israelis says, this shows that\N{\rChinese}以色列人说，这表明
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.68,0:03:14.08,English,,0,0,0,,our Iron Dome system is amazing.\N{\rChinese}我们的铁穹系统很棒。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.30,0:03:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,We're amazing. Iran cannot touch us.\N{\rChinese}我们很棒，伊朗碰不到我们。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:20.82,English,,0,0,0,,What the Iranians said is that, no,\N{\rChinese}伊朗人说的是，没错，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.96,0:03:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,we designed the attack.\N{\rChinese}我们设计了这次攻击。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.16,0:03:27.48,English,,0,0,0,,We're not going to attack Iran. We govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}我们不打伊朗，我们治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.48,0:03:29.24,English,,0,0,0,,We govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}我们治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.50,0:03:31.34,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.34,0:03:32.26,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.26,0:03:39.70,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.86,0:03:41.38,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:43.66,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran. govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.78,0:03:49.10,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran. govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.56,0:03:51.72,English,,0,0,0,,govern Iran.\N{\rChinese}治理伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.42,0:03:54.90,English,,0,0,0,,and the Israelis.\N{\rChinese}以及以色列人。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.24,0:03:58.30,English,,0,0,0,,And the reason why is the Americans\N{\rChinese}而原因是美国人。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:04:01.00,English,,0,0,0,,and the Israelis have military dominance over\N{\rChinese}以及以色列人拥有军事优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:05.14,English,,0,0,0,,Iran. But just because\N{\rChinese}伊朗。只是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:08.60,English,,0,0,0,,you have military dominance does not mean you'll win the war.\N{\rChinese}你拥有军事优势并不代表你能赢得战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.04,0:04:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what I believe is that\N{\rChinese}好的？所以我认为是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.72,0:04:15.94,English,,0,0,0,,Iran and Israel are committed to a war and\N{\rChinese}伊朗与以色列已投入战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:20.78,English,,0,0,0,,it's possible that in two years time there will be a ground invasion of Iran.\N{\rChinese}有可能在两年后伊朗会被陆军入侵。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:24.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, but it's gonna take time to build up to the ground invasion.\N{\rChinese}好的，但要把陆军入侵准备好还需要一段时间。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.34,0:04:28.52,English,,0,0,0,,But just because the Americans and\N{\rChinese}但仅仅因为美国和
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.52,0:04:32.02,English,,0,0,0,,Israelis attack Iran does not mean they will win.\N{\rChinese}以色列人攻击伊朗并不意味着他们会赢。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.18,0:04:34.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, and the reason why is that\N{\rChinese}好的，原因在于
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.14,0:04:38.44,English,,0,0,0,,as you know from your research in 2002 the Americans actually\N{\rChinese}正如你在2002年的研究中所知，美国实际上
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,tried to invade Iran.\N{\rChinese}尝试入侵伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.42,0:04:49.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, they had they run a simulation called the 2002 Millennium Challenge\N{\rChinese}好的，他们曾进行过一次名为2002年千禧挑战的模拟。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:51.52,English,,0,0,0,,and the idea is let's pretend\N{\rChinese}并且想法是让我们假设我们将入侵伊朗，看看会怎样。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:54.56,English,,0,0,0,,that we will invade Iran and let's see what happens.\N{\rChinese}that we will invade Iran and let's see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.80,0:04:57.50,English,,0,0,0,,So they divide the military into two teams, right?\N{\rChinese}于是他们把军队分成两组，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.62,0:04:59.02,English,,0,0,0,,Team USA and\N{\rChinese}美国组
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.96,0:05:05.44,English,,0,0,0,,Team Iran. Now if you know anything about the American military,\N{\rChinese}伊朗组。现在如果你了解美国军队的情况，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.78,0:05:07.60,English,,0,0,0,,you will know that it is the most\N{\rChinese}你会知道它是最强大的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.38,0:05:12.74,English,,0,0,0,,dominant powerful military ever to exist in human history.\N{\rChinese}人类历史上最强大的军队。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.88,0:05:14.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, it is crazy powerful.\N{\rChinese}好的，它非常强大。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.84,0:05:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,If the entire world were to get together and\N{\rChinese}如果全世界聚在一起并
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.50,0:05:20.68,English,,0,0,0,,say let's go fight the United States.\N{\rChinese}说吧，去跟美国打一场。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,The world would lose. The United States has the most powerful military in the entire world.\N{\rChinese}世界会输。美国拥有全世界最强大的军队。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.58,0:05:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, and Iran It's a very poor country.\N{\rChinese}好的，伊朗是个非常贫穷的国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.58,0:05:36.62,English,,0,0,0,,So the United States invaded Iran and\N{\rChinese}于是美国入侵伊朗并
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.62,0:05:41.30,English,,0,0,0,,they wanted to see what would happen and it turned out that who won?\N{\rChinese}他们想看看会怎样，结果谁赢了？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.74,0:05:44.52,English,,0,0,0,,Iran won. Okay, and\N{\rChinese}伊朗赢了。好的，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.52,0:05:48.80,English,,0,0,0,,the reason why Iran won is the idea of asymmetrical warfare.\N{\rChinese}伊朗之胜的原因在于非对称作战的理念。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.20,0:05:56.82,English,,0,0,0,,All right, and this is very important idea that\N{\rChinese}好了，这个理念非常重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.82,0:05:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,you must know if you are to understand this conflict.\N{\rChinese}你必须知道这一点，才能理解这场冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:01.94,English,,0,0,0,,So what is asymmetrical warfare?\N{\rChinese}那么，什么是非对称作战？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.28,0:06:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,All right, let's pretend that Jack and I are enemies.\N{\rChinese}好了，假设杰克和我是敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:07.84,English,,0,0,0,,We hate each other and want to kill each other.\N{\rChinese}我们互相仇恨，想互相杀死。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.90,0:06:10.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Jack has armor\N{\rChinese}好的？杰克穿着盔甲。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.58,0:06:12.72,English,,0,0,0,,and he has a machine gun.\N{\rChinese}他还有机枪。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.18,0:06:14.68,English,,0,0,0,,I have nothing.\N{\rChinese}我什么都没有。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.80,0:06:17.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so in most battles\N{\rChinese}好的，基本上大多数战斗是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.16,0:06:19.36,English,,0,0,0,,Jack's gonna kill me, right?\N{\rChinese}杰克要杀我，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.04,0:06:25.02,English,,0,0,0,,But let's pretend that I live in a dark forest\N{\rChinese}但让我们假设我住在一片黑暗的森林里
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.02,0:06:29.52,English,,0,0,0,,and it's really hard to see in this dark forest But I've been living there for decades.\N{\rChinese}并且在这片黑暗的森林里很难看清楚，但我已经在那里住了几十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.88,0:06:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I know it's dark forest very very well\N{\rChinese}好的，我对这片黑暗的森林非常非常熟悉。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.24,0:06:35.64,English,,0,0,0,,So if Jack attacks me in this dark forest\N{\rChinese}如果杰克在这片黑暗的森林里攻击我
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.28,0:06:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,Then it's possible for me to win because I can set traps, right?\N{\rChinese}那我就有可能获胜，因为我可以设置陷阱，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:41.60,English,,0,0,0,,I can play tricks on\N{\rChinese}我可以对杰克玩些诡计
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,Jack and that's the idea of asymmetrical warfare.\N{\rChinese}这就是不对称战争的核心
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, even though Jack is superior\N{\rChinese}好的，虽然杰克更强
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.40,0:06:51.62,English,,0,0,0,,Because I'm inferior.\N{\rChinese}因为我更弱
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.94,0:06:53.40,English,,0,0,0,,I'm forced to be much more\N{\rChinese}我被迫在对付杰克时更具战略性，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.04,0:06:57.66,English,,0,0,0,,strategic in how I fight against Jack, okay?\N{\rChinese}strategic in how I fight against Jack, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.30,0:07:03.12,English,,0,0,0,,and so asymmetrical warfare means\N{\rChinese}而不对称战争的含义是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.12,0:07:05.90,English,,0,0,0,,that as long as you can define the\N{\rChinese}只要你能定义它为
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:09.88,English,,0,0,0,,terms of engagement as long as you can\N{\rChinese}交战条件只要你能
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.56,0:07:14.74,English,,0,0,0,,Control how the war is fought you will win\N{\rChinese}掌握战争方式，你就能赢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.42,0:07:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's look\N{\rChinese}好的，那我们来看看
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:21.82,English,,0,0,0,,at what this means for Iran and the United States.\N{\rChinese}这对伊朗和美国意味着什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:25.76,English,,0,0,0,,So the United States has these aircraft carriers\N{\rChinese}美国拥有这些航空母舰
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:33.56,English,,0,0,0,,And they cost like a billion dollars, okay, they're very expensive but they're very powerful\N{\rChinese}它们的造价约十亿美元，十分昂贵，但极其强大
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.34,0:07:38.30,English,,0,0,0,,now in a symmetrical warfare what happened is\N{\rChinese}现在在对称战争中发生的事是
