Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:03.28,English,,0,0,0,,you win the war depending on how...\N{\rChinese}你赢得战争取决于……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.68,0:16:07.18,English,,0,0,0,,how much your population is willing to resist the invasion.\N{\rChinese}你的人口愿意抵抗入侵的程度如何？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.82,0:16:11.36,English,,0,0,0,,And it turns out that even though the Iranians right now are divided,\N{\rChinese}结果显示，尽管伊朗人现在分裂，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.52,0:16:14.86,English,,0,0,0,,there's a lot of opposition towards the current government in Iran.\N{\rChinese}在伊朗，现政府面临大规模反对派势力。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,As some of you know, there have been some protests over the past few years.\N{\rChinese}正如你们所知，近数年间已有多次示威。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.34,0:16:22.80,English,,0,0,0,,Women protesting for more rights in Iran.\N{\rChinese}妇女在伊朗为争取更多权利而示威。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.14,0:16:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,So there's a lot of division in that country.\N{\rChinese}于是该国内部出现了大规模分裂。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.12,0:16:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,But I think that\N{\rChinese}我认为……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.44,0:16:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,most Iranians would resist an invasion.\N{\rChinese}大多数伊朗人会抵抗入侵。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.86,0:16:33.66,English,,0,0,0,,The reason why is...\N{\rChinese}原因是……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,that the Iranians have a very bad history with Westerners. So\N{\rChinese}伊朗人和西方人有着很久的历史恩怨。于是……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,the example is the 1953 coup d 'etat.\N{\rChinese}1953年的政变就是例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.54,0:16:50.16,English,,0,0,0,,So what happened is that in 1909,\N{\rChinese}于是发生的事是，1909年，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:54.16,English,,0,0,0,,the British discovered oil in Iran.\N{\rChinese}英国人在伊朗发现了油田。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.46,0:16:56.30,English,,0,0,0,,It was called Persia back then.\N{\rChinese}当时它被称为波斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.50,0:16:58.12,English,,0,0,0,,So they created a company\N{\rChinese}于是他们创建了一家公司
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.12,0:17:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,called the Anglo -Iranian Oil Company.\N{\rChinese}叫做英伊石油公司。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.68,0:17:07.22,English,,0,0,0,,Petroleum company, which we now know as British Petroleum, BP.\N{\rChinese}石油公司，后来我们知道的英国石油公司，BP。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.86,0:17:11.02,English,,0,0,0,,And the idea is that\N{\rChinese}其想法是
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:15.50,English,,0,0,0,,this company would be responsible for extracting and selling all the oil.\N{\rChinese}这家公司负责开采并出售所有油料。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:20.42,English,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately, the deal was that\N{\rChinese}但不幸的是，协议是
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.42,0:17:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,Iran, Persia,\N{\rChinese}伊朗，波斯王国，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.96,0:17:25.24,English,,0,0,0,,would only get 16% of profits.\N{\rChinese}只获得16%的利润。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.22,0:17:28.22,English,,0,0,0,,They only got 16% of profits.\N{\rChinese}他们只拿到16%的利润。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.98,0:17:32.52,English,,0,0,0,,So the Iranians are very upset about this.\N{\rChinese}于是伊朗人对此非常不满。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.52,0:17:33.76,English,,0,0,0,,It's their oil.\N{\rChinese}那是他们的油。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.28,0:17:37.78,English,,0,0,0,,It's their resource. But they're not getting that much money out of it.\N{\rChinese}那是他们的资源，但他们从中拿不到那么多钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:40.72,English,,0,0,0,,It's basically stealing. So for decades,\N{\rChinese}这基本就是抢夺。于是几十年间，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.28,0:17:44.48,English,,0,0,0,,the Iranians have been trying to renegotiate the deal.\N{\rChinese}伊朗人一直在尝试重新谈判这笔交易。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:50.06,English,,0,0,0,,In 1953, the democratically elected government of Iran said to the British,\N{\rChinese}1953年，伊朗民选政府对英国人说：
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.24,0:17:52.40,English,,0,0,0,,Listen, let's do 50 -50.\N{\rChinese}听着，来50-50吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:55.70,English,,0,0,0,,That's fair. 50 -50.\N{\rChinese}这算公平。50-50。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.76,0:17:58.82,English,,0,0,0,,50% for us, 50% for you.\N{\rChinese}50%给我们，50%给你们。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.94,0:18:02.18,English,,0,0,0,,That's a fair deal. And the British, instead of saying yes,\N{\rChinese}这算公平。英国人于是说是。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:04.54,English,,0,0,0,,said, Let's do 50 -50. And the British and\N{\rChinese}说，来50-50吧。英国人和
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.54,0:18:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,the Americans together launched a coup d 'etat\N{\rChinese}美国人一起发动政变
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:10.92,English,,0,0,0,,against the democratically elected government of Iran\N{\rChinese}对伊朗民选政府的对抗
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.92,0:18:14.32,English,,0,0,0,,and installed a police state called the Shah.\N{\rChinese}并建立了被称为沙阿的警察国家
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.36,0:18:19.58,English,,0,0,0,,The Shah. Which is like the monarchy.\N{\rChinese}沙阿，类似于君主制。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:23.00,English,,0,0,0,,And the Shah, the king of Iran,\N{\rChinese}沙阿，伊朗的国王。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.26,0:18:26.62,English,,0,0,0,,was so brutal that he created a police state.\N{\rChinese}那场斗争如此残酷，以至建立了警察国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.26,0:18:32.28,English,,0,0,0,,In 1979, the Iranian people overthrew the Shah.\N{\rChinese}1979年，伊朗人民推翻了沙阿。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:34.46,English,,0,0,0,,And so\N{\rChinese}于是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,the Iranian people do not like the\N{\rChinese}伊朗人民不喜欢外来侵略者占据资源的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:42.30,English,,0,0,0,,idea of foreign invaders coming in and controlling the resources.\N{\rChinese}idea of foreign invaders comingin and controlling the resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.50,0:18:46.06,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? So over time,\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？于是，随着时间的推移，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:47.94,English,,0,0,0,,as Israel and\N{\rChinese}以色列和
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:52.38,English,,0,0,0,,as America continues to be aggressive towards Iran,\N{\rChinese}以美继续对伊朗发起攻势，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.68,0:18:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,the population will start to coalesce\N{\rChinese}人们将开始聚合
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.24,0:18:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,and fight against the Americans.\N{\rChinese}并与美国作战。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:01.24,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the United Population.\N{\rChinese}于是就是统一的人口。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.24,0:19:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,Second is build alliances.\N{\rChinese}第二层是建盟友。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.80,0:19:07.88,English,,0,0,0,,Now, Iran has two layers of alliance.\N{\rChinese}现在，伊朗有两层联盟。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.18,0:19:11.52,English,,0,0,0,,The first layer is called the Axis of Resistance, right?\N{\rChinese}第一层叫做抗战轴线，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:15.82,English,,0,0,0,,Which I asked you to research.\N{\rChinese}我请你去研究的那一层。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.42,0:19:17.90,English,,0,0,0,,And the Axis of Resistance\N{\rChinese}以及抗战轴线
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,includes the Shia\N{\rChinese}包括什叶派
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.36,0:19:25.78,English,,0,0,0,,militias in Iraq, Syria,\N{\rChinese}伊拉克、叙利亚的民兵，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.32,0:19:27.80,English,,0,0,0,,Hezbollah in Lebanon,\N{\rChinese}黎巴嫩的真哈瓦德，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.16,0:19:30.92,English,,0,0,0,,Hamas, and the Houthis in Yemen.\N{\rChinese}哈马斯和也门的胡塞组织。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.24,0:19:35.66,English,,0,0,0,,Now, what's important to understand is that this is not an alliance.\N{\rChinese}现在，重要的是要明白这不是一个联盟。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.30,0:19:39.66,English,,0,0,0,,Sorry. What's important to understand is that this is an alliance.\N{\rChinese}抱歉。重要的是要明白这是一场联盟。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:42.70,English,,0,0,0,,They agree to fight together because\N{\rChinese}他们同意一起作战。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:44.62,English,,0,0,0,,they have common interests, which\N{\rChinese}它们有共同的利益，即
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.62,0:19:49.84,English,,0,0,0,,is to remain independent of American influence.\N{\rChinese}保持独立于美国影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.30,0:19:54.00,English,,0,0,0,,But that does not mean that\N{\rChinese}但这并不意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.00,0:19:57.20,English,,0,0,0,,Hamas, Hezbollah, and Houthis take orders from Iran.\N{\rChinese}哈马斯、真纳和胡塞都听从伊朗指挥。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.20,0:19:59.84,English,,0,0,0,,They're not controlled by Iran.\N{\rChinese}它们并非被伊朗掌控。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,Iran supports them militarily and financially,\N{\rChinese}伊朗在军力和经费上支持它们。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.00,0:20:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,but Iran cannot completely control their behavior.\N{\rChinese}但伊朗并不能完全掌控它们的行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.26,0:20:09.42,English,,0,0,0,,So the example is, on October 7th,\N{\rChinese}比如说，10月7日，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.42,0:20:13.28,English,,0,0,0,,Hamas launched an attack against Israel, right?\N{\rChinese}哈马斯向以色列发动了攻击，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.42,0:20:15.04,English,,0,0,0,,Which resulted in this war.\N{\rChinese}这导致了这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.70,0:20:18.18,English,,0,0,0,,And Iran says, we were not involved.\N{\rChinese}伊朗则说，自己并未参与。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.04,0:20:22.32,English,,0,0,0,,And Israel says, that can't be true\N{\rChinese}以色列则说，这不可能是真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.32,0:20:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,because you control Hamas.\N{\rChinese}因为你掌控哈马斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.66,0:20:28.60,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the first layer of alliance.\N{\rChinese}所以这就是联盟的第一层。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.60,0:20:31.96,English,,0,0,0,,But what Iran needs to do,\N{\rChinese}但伊朗需要做的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.16,0:20:36.74,English,,0,0,0,,if it is to win the war, is also bring in Russia and China.\N{\rChinese}如果要赢得这场战争，还要拉入俄罗斯和中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:46.22,English,,0,0,0,,Russia wants the United States to fight Iran.\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯希望美国去对抗伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.40,0:20:51.22,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Yeah,\N{\rChinese}为什么？是啊，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.30,0:20:55.00,English,,0,0,0,,but, true, to distract and weaken the United States,\N{\rChinese}但，确实如此，为了分散并削弱美国，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.06,0:21:00.36,English,,0,0,0,,and also to move the attention away from Ukraine, right?\N{\rChinese}并且把注意力转移到乌克兰之外，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.84,0:21:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Because Russia is about to win the war in Ukraine,\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？因为俄罗斯正要在乌克兰赢得战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.94,0:21:06.94,English,,0,0,0,,and if there's a war in Iran, then\N{\rChinese}如果伊朗爆发战争，那么
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.94,0:21:12.20,English,,0,0,0,,the United States will be forced to divert resources away from Ukraine into Iran,\N{\rChinese}美国将被迫把资源从乌克兰调往伊朗，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.34,0:21:15.74,English,,0,0,0,,okay? What would Russia bring to the table?\N{\rChinese}好的？俄罗斯会带来什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.90,0:21:18.74,English,,0,0,0,,Russia would probably not deploy soldiers, okay?\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯大概不会派兵，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.96,0:21:21.52,English,,0,0,0,,But what Russia would do is say to the United States,\N{\rChinese}但俄罗斯会这么说：
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.48,0:21:24.50,English,,0,0,0,,when you invade Iran,\N{\rChinese}当你入侵伊朗时，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.50,0:21:29.24,English,,0,0,0,,you are not allowed to use tactical nuclear weapons,\N{\rChinese}你们不可以使用战术核武器，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.40,0:21:30.74,English,,0,0,0,,okay? You understand?\N{\rChinese}好的？你明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.32,0:21:34.20,English,,0,0,0,,Russia would say that, hey, hey, hey, United States,\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯会这么说，嘿，嘿，嘿，美国，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.30,0:21:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,if you use weapons, nuclear weapons, against Iran,\N{\rChinese}如果你用武器，核武器，对付伊朗，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.16,0:21:39.60,English,,0,0,0,,we will use nuclear weapons against you, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们会用核武器打你，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.10,0:21:41.14,English,,0,0,0,,So basically,\N{\rChinese}所以基本上，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.34,0:21:46.40,English,,0,0,0,,Russia would limit the military options of America in a war,\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯会在战争中限制美国的军事选择
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:49.46,English,,0,0,0,,which would be of tremendous benefit and advantage to Iran.\N{\rChinese}这将为伊朗带来巨大的利益和优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:54.48,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? China needs to help Iran.\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？中国需要帮助伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.50,0:21:58.74,English,,0,0,0,,Why? What does Iran have that China really needs?\N{\rChinese}为什么？伊朗有什么中国真正需要的？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.16,0:22:06.46,English,,0,0,0,,What does Iran have that China really, really needs?\N{\rChinese}伊朗有什么中国真正、真正需要的？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.78,0:22:08.00,English,,0,0,0,,It really needs this.\N{\rChinese}它真的需要这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.38,0:22:13.10,English,,0,0,0,,The Chinese economy needs what?\N{\rChinese}中国经济需要什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.36,0:22:18.82,English,,0,0,0,,Oil, right? So\N{\rChinese}油吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.82,0:22:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,basically, China can afford for the United States to take over both Iraq\N{\rChinese}基本上，中国可以让美国接管伊拉克两国
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:24.62,English,,0,0,0,,and Iran, because then\N{\rChinese}以及伊朗，因为接着
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.62,0:22:28.48,English,,0,0,0,,it can control the energy supply to China.\N{\rChinese}它可以控制能源供应给中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.62,0:22:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? So\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？所以
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.14,0:22:35.06,English,,0,0,0,,China would involve itself over time in order to make sure\N{\rChinese}中国会在一段时间内介入，以确保
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.54,0:22:39.18,English,,0,0,0,,that it's able to obtain oil from the Middle East.\N{\rChinese}它能够从中东获得石油。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.96,0:22:45.40,English,,0,0,0,,China right now is getting most of its oil from the Middle East, okay? But\N{\rChinese}现在中国大部分石油来自中东，好吗？但
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.40,0:22:50.92,English,,0,0,0,,it will take time for Russia\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯需要时间
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.92,0:22:52.58,English,,0,0,0,,and China to get themselves involved.\N{\rChinese}中国也需要时间介入。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.58,0:22:56.70,English,,0,0,0,,For Russia and China to get themselves involved in this conflict,\N{\rChinese}为了让俄罗斯和中国介入这场冲突，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.98,0:22:58.52,English,,0,0,0,,Iran must prove two things.\N{\rChinese}伊朗必须证明两件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.74,0:22:59.74,English,,0,0,0,,What are these two things?\N{\rChinese}这两件事是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.62,0:23:07.98,English,,0,0,0,,What must Iran show to China and\N{\rChinese}伊朗必须向中国和俄罗斯展示什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.98,0:23:12.28,English,,0,0,0,,Russia in order to get China and Russia involved in this conflict?\N{\rChinese}以便让中国和俄罗斯介入这场冲突？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.28,0:23:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,If you're China and Russia, you're an investor, right?\N{\rChinese}如果你是中国和俄罗斯，你就是投资者，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.98,0:23:19.98,English,,0,0,0,,Why will I invest in you, Iran?\N{\rChinese}为什么我要投资你，伊朗？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:23.10,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Why? Because you're an investor.\N{\rChinese}为什么？为什么？因为你是投资者。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.20,0:23:26.46,English,,0,0,0,,Exactly, okay? So the first thing is we will fight.\N{\rChinese}对，没错。第一件事是我们会战斗。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.62,0:23:28.96,English,,0,0,0,,Second thing is we will win, okay?\N{\rChinese}第二件事是我们会赢，没错？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.10,0:23:31.68,English,,0,0,0,,So this will take time for Iran\N{\rChinese}于是这件事会花时间让伊朗证明给俄罗斯听见
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.68,0:23:35.72,English,,0,0,0,,to prove this to Russia\N{\rChinese}to prove this toRussia
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.72,0:23:38.42,English,,0,0,0,,and China. And the more that\N{\rChinese}和中国。越多……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.42,0:23:41.44,English,,0,0,0,,Iran can show it can win, the more that\N{\rChinese}伊朗能展示其胜利，越多……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.44,0:23:44.14,English,,0,0,0,,China and Russia will invest in Iran,\N{\rChinese}中国和俄罗斯将越多投资伊朗
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.36,0:23:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,both financially and militarily and politically, okay?\N{\rChinese}两方面都包括财政、军事和政治，没错？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.94,0:23:49.22,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Okay, so this will take time.\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？好吧，这会花时间。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.58,0:23:52.56,English,,0,0,0,,And the third thing is win global war.\N{\rChinese}第三件事是赢得全球战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.16,0:23:57.76,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern govern govern\N{\rChinese}治理治理治理治理
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.66,0:23:59.94,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern govern\N{\rChinese}治理治理治理
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.06,0:24:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern govern govern govern govern\N{\rChinese}治理治理治理治理治理治理
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.84,0:24:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern govern govern govern govern govern govern\N{\rChinese}治理治理治理治理治理治理治理治理
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.44,0:24:23.50,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern govern thing is happening right now\N{\rChinese}治理治理治理事情正在发生现在
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.50,0:24:25.92,English,,0,0,0,,that is outraging or angering the world?\N{\rChinese}那正是让世界惊叹或愤怒的事？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.72,0:24:36.36,English,,0,0,0,,What's happening right now? What's Israel doing right now that is outraging the world?\N{\rChinese}现在发生了什么？以色列现在在做什么让世界惊叹？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.10,0:24:41.22,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Gaza, okay? So\N{\rChinese}是的，戛撒，好的？所以……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.22,0:24:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,this is really important for Iran.\N{\rChinese}这对伊朗来说真的很重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.98,0:24:48.60,English,,0,0,0,,It must maintain the world spotlight on Gaza,\N{\rChinese}它必须让世界的聚光继续聚焦在加沙，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.98,0:24:52.26,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Because what's happening in Gaza, it's basically genocide,\N{\rChinese}好的？因为加沙正在发生的事，基本就是大屠杀，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.70,0:24:57.78,English,,0,0,0,,right? Where the Israelis are committed to solving the Palestinian problem once\N{\rChinese}对吗？以色列正致力一次性解决巴勒斯坦问题
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.78,0:25:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,and for all. That basically means removing the Palestinians from Gaza.\N{\rChinese}并且对所有人而言。基本就是把巴勒斯坦人从加沙搬走。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.04,0:25:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,They can go to Egypt.\N{\rChinese}他们可以去埃及。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.68,0:25:06.24,English,,0,0,0,,They can go to Jordan. It doesn't matter.\N{\rChinese}他们可以去约旦。没什么区别。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.38,0:25:09.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But the Israelis want them out of Gaza.\N{\rChinese}好的？但以色列人想把他们从加沙搬走。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.12,0:25:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And so this will go on for many, many years.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是这件事会持续好几年。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.82,0:25:17.88,English,,0,0,0,,And as long as the attention is on Gaza.\N{\rChinese}只要注意力一直聚焦在加沙。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.88,0:25:22.54,English,,0,0,0,,then people will become much more sympathetic towards Iran over time.\N{\rChinese}于是人们会随着时间对伊朗产生更深的同情。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.38,0:25:25.66,English,,0,0,0,,If you've been following the news about America,\N{\rChinese}如果你一直关注美国的新闻，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.90,0:25:29.38,English,,0,0,0,,there have been major protests at Yale\N{\rChinese}在耶鲁大学已经出现大规模示威。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.38,0:25:32.86,English,,0,0,0,,and at Columbia and other universities about what's happening in Gaza.\N{\rChinese}在哥伦比亚大学和其他高校讨论加沙的情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.66,0:25:38.42,English,,0,0,0,,And the last is weaken the enemy.\N{\rChinese}最后一点是削弱敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.66,0:25:39.96,English,,0,0,0,,So what does this mean?\N{\rChinese}那这意味着什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.06,0:25:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,It means that when the United States invades Iran,\N{\rChinese}这意味着当美国入侵伊朗时，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.96,0:25:47.94,English,,0,0,0,,two years from now, six years from now, who knows, but when\N{\rChinese}两年后，六年后，谁知道，但当……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.94,0:25:51.50,English,,0,0,0,,it does, so, it wants to build a large coalition of forces,\N{\rChinese}它完成后，它想组建一个大联盟的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.80,0:25:54.26,English,,0,0,0,,okay, because then, it gives, because, then,\N{\rChinese}好的，因为这样，它就给自己合法性，右边，所以，这个
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.30,0:25:56.72,English,,0,0,0,,it gives itself legitimacy, right, so, this,\N{\rChinese}it gives itself legitimacy, right, so, this,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.72,0:26:00.22,English,,0,0,0,,this coalition, will,\N{\rChinese}这个联盟将，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.36,0:26:04.66,English,,0,0,0,,consist, of, NATO, Middle East, countries, right,\N{\rChinese}由北约中东国家组成，对吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.06,0:26:11.18,English,,0,0,0,,and, Israel, Saudi, Arabia, many, many,\N{\rChinese}和以色列、沙特尔、阿拉伯、许多、许多，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.20,0:26:14.92,English,,0,0,0,,countries, and, what, Iran, needs, to, do, is,\N{\rChinese}国家，和，伊朗需要做的事是，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.64,0:26:20.18,English,,0,0,0,,create, a, conflict and dissent in this coalition.\N{\rChinese}创建内部纷争与分歧
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.28,0:26:23.40,English,,0,0,0,,And the way it does that\N{\rChinese}并以此方式实现
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.40,0:26:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,is by building up internal dissent.\N{\rChinese}通过内部纷争来实现。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.70,0:26:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}这样说对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.68,0:26:38.92,English,,0,0,0,,There are many people, most people in America do not support a war against Iran.\N{\rChinese}有很多人，绝大多数美国人不支持对伊朗的战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.94,0:26:44.66,English,,0,0,0,,And so Iran needs to encourage this internal dissent.\N{\rChinese}于是伊朗需要激发内部纷争。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.40,0:26:50.98,English,,0,0,0,,It can also create conflict between NATO\N{\rChinese}它也能在北约与美国之间制造冲突，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.98,0:26:53.22,English,,0,0,0,,and the United States, okay?\N{\rChinese}因为显然，美国会想让北约参与对伊朗的入侵。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.66,0:26:58.58,English,,0,0,0,,Because obviously, America will want NATO involved in its invasion of Iran,\N{\rChinese}Because obviously, America will wantNATO involved in its invasion of Iran,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.86,0:27:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,but why would France and Germany want to involve itself, right?\N{\rChinese}但为什么法国和德国会想要介入呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.42,0:27:05.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, does that make sense? So\N{\rChinese}好，明白了？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.40,0:27:09.76,English,,0,0,0,,these are the four major goals of Iran,\N{\rChinese}这些就是伊朗的四大目标。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.00,0:27:14.58,English,,0,0,0,,and it must accomplish all four goals,\N{\rChinese}并且要完成这四个目标，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.12,0:27:17.48,English,,0,0,0,,if it is to survive, if it is to survive an invasion,\N{\rChinese}如果它要存活，如果它要在入侵中存活，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.94,0:27:21.70,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So from now on, everything that Iran does\N{\rChinese}好，接下来伊朗所做的一切都…
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.54,0:27:24.80,English,,0,0,0,,will be to accomplish all four goals, okay?\N{\rChinese}将完成这四个目标，明白了？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.86,0:27:27.66,English,,0,0,0,,And this is part of asymmetrical warfare.\N{\rChinese}这属于非对称作战的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.80,0:27:33.54,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? All right, now let's look at a concrete example.\N{\rChinese}明白了？现在我们来看一个具体例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.82,0:27:38.72,English,,0,0,0,,The concrete example is Operation True Promise.\N{\rChinese}具体例子是“真诚承诺”行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.06,0:27:43.84,English,,0,0,0,,Why did Iran design Operation True Promise the way it did?\N{\rChinese}伊朗为什么把“真诚承诺”行动设计成这样？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.02,0:27:48.06,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is, to accomplish all four goals, right?\N{\rChinese}答案是：为了完成这四个目标，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.18,0:27:49.92,English,,0,0,0,,The first is unite the population.\N{\rChinese}第一点是团结民众。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.22,0:27:54.74,English,,0,0,0,,The idea here is Iran needed to show its population\N{\rChinese}这里的想法是伊朗需要向其民众展示其能对以色列反击。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.74,0:27:58.32,English,,0,0,0,,that Iran can strike back against Israel, okay?\N{\rChinese}这样做能让伊朗民众看到其有能力反击以色列。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.38,0:28:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the first thing. Build alliances.\N{\rChinese}于是第一件事就是组建同盟。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.16,0:28:07.82,English,,0,0,0,,Striking Israel is showing its allies\N{\rChinese}打击以色列是向其盟友展示的。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.82,0:28:11.50,English,,0,0,0,,and to China and Russia that Iran is willing to fight, okay?\N{\rChinese}并向中俄表明伊朗愿意作战，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.90,0:28:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,When the law of the world is in place,\N{\rChinese}当世界法则已成形，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.22,0:28:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern govern\N{\rChinese}治理治理治理
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.64,0:28:21.46,English,,0,0,0,,govern govern\N{\rChinese}治理治理
